  "text": "It may also be that TI is ineffective against predators that specialise on a given prey type and have, thus, been able to coevolve effective responses to TI. As an example of this, [CITATION_1] demonstrated TI in the grass snake (Natrix natrix) and hypothesised that this would only be an effective tactic against generalist predators that rarely encounter it. From this, Gregory et al. then suggested that grass snakes should less readily show TI in those parts of its range shared by the snake specialist short-toed eagle (Circaetus gallicus).",
